  sodium: 730 mg
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/spiced-maple-ricotta-cherry-toasts-6539090665bc5aac330e0614
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: North America
---

Wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Roughly chop @cashews{1/2%ounce}. Halve, core, and
cut @apple{1} into ¼-inch-thick slices.

In a small #bowl{}, combine @dried cherries{1%ounce}, 1 TBSP water, and a squeeze
of lemon juice (2 TBSP water and a big squeeze of lemon juice for 4 servings);
cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Remove plastic wrap
and pour off liquid. Set aside until ready to serve.

Toast @sourdough bread{4%slices} in a #toaster{}.

In a second small bowl, whisk together @ricotta cheese{4%oz}, @cream cheese{4%tbsp},
@maple syrup{2%tbsp}, @warming spice blend{1%tbsp}, and a pinch of @salt{} until
combined.

> Be sure to measure the Warming Spice Blend; we sent more!

Spread ricotta mixture on toasts; top with @cherry jam{1}, drained cherries,
cashews, and lemon zest.

Divide toasts between #plates{} and serve with apple slices on the side.